Japan Provides Grants to Senegal for Food, Schools, Soleil Says

-- B y   D r e w   H i n s h a w
-- 
2011-03-09T09:48:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/japan-provides-grants-to-senegal-for-food-schools-soleil-says.html
Japan signed three accords with
Senegal yesterday granting the West African nation 18.2 billion  CFA francs  ($38.5 million) to boost food supplies and improve
education, Le Soleil reported.  The grants include 5 billion CFA francs to stabilize food
supplies, the Dakar-based newspaper said, citing the agreements.
The remaining 13.2 billion will be dedicated to building primary
and vocational schools, Le Soleil reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Hinshaw in Dakar via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 